    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-04-02T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-04-02T11:00:00-05:00" n="123"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.01/344a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-02T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 2, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Your 17, April 1, 1 p.m. You are authorized to proceed to Burgos for informal
                    and unofficial conversations in connection with protection of American interests
                    with authorities at Burgos. Report fully on conversations upon your return to
                    Seville.</p>
                <p>For your own information this Government does not recognize the Franco regime,
                    nor is your visit to Burgos to be construed in any way as such recognition.</p>
                <p>Report date of departure and return to your post. Transportation expenses and
                    $6.00 per diem authorized subject travel regulations chargeable “Transportation
                    Foreign Service Officers, 1938”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
